commit.message:
Don't allow empty namespace names

For example, an attribute :class was parsed as having an empty
namespace, with local name "class". It is now parsed as no namespace,
local name ":class". Per the namespace spec at

  https://www.w3.org/TR/xml-names/#iri-use

> The empty string, though it is a legal URI reference, cannot be used
> as a namespace name.

Fixes https://github.com/aantron/lambdasoup/issues/39.

opam files: don't track package version

[skip ci]

XML tokenizer: fix reading of numeric references

Fixes #65.

Remove remaining mentions of content_signal

Resolves #60.

Remove version link from README

[skip ci]

Markup.pretty_print: add newline after doctype

Fixes #58.

Delete type content_signal and some row types

Resolves #59.
Travis: update OCaml and opam, other fixes

HTML writer: preserve the doctype

The HTML5 spec requires outputting <!DOCTYPE html> as the doctype.
However, Markup.ml already has a helper (Markup.html5) for replacing any
doctype with the HTML5 doctype. So, it is better for the writer to
output whatever doctype is present in the signal stream, trusting the
user to call Markup.html5 if it is necessary for their purpose.

Part of aantron/lambdasoup#37.

Fix parsing of ruby tags

Resolves #56.
